==English==

===Etymology===
From Standard Hebrew אָדָם (adam) "earth" or "man", "soil" or "light brown"; [[אדמה]] (adamah) 'red earth', 'ground'.
 Arabic آدم, Adam, አዳም (Adam) in Geez);

===Proper noun===
'''Adam'''

# The first man in the [[Bible]] and the [[Koran]], the [[progenitor]] of the [[human race]]. Together with [[Eve]] he became father of their two sons [[Cain]] and [[Abel]].
# A male [[given name]].
# (''figuratively'') [[Original sin]]; human frailty.
# (''figuratively'') Verbal slang - "No Adam" is used to represent homosexuality.

